      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "freshly squeezed"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "or to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon",
      "notes": "or to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit",
    "In a large kadhai, melt 2 tablespoons of salted butter over medium heat",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute",
    "Stir in the crushed turkish red pepper and cook for 1 minute",
    "Add the confit tomatoes, chicken broth, salt, and black pepper, and bring to a simmer",
    "Roast the firm white fish in the oven with the remaining 2 tablespoons of salted butter for 8 minutes, or until cooked through",
    "Add the roasted fish to the kadhai and stir to combine",
    "Squeeze the lemon juice over the top and sprinkle with chopped parsley",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired"
  ],
